  "prompt": "What are the legal precedents related to money laundering cases?",
  "response": "Here are some key legal precedents related to money laundering cases:\n\n1. Bank Secrecy Act (BSA) Precedents\n- Established reporting requirements\n- Required financial institutions to report suspicious transactions\n- Provides framework for anti-money laundering investigations\n\n2. Notable Supreme Court Cases\n- United States v. Santos (2008)\n- Defined money laundering transaction definitions\n- Clarified interpretations of financial criminal statutes\n\n3. Major Federal Prosecutions\n- HSBC Bank money laundering settlement (2012)\n- Large financial penalties for inadequate compliance\n- Demonstrated enforcement of international banking regulations\n\n4. Key Prosecution Strategies\n- Proving intent\n- Tracing financial transactions\n- Demonstrating knowledge of illegal source of funds\n\n5. International Cooperation Precedents\n- Mutual Legal Assistance Treaties\n- Cross-border investigation protocols\n- Extradition agreements for financial crimes\n\nThese are general legal precedents. For specific legal advice, I recommend consulting a qualified attorney specializing in financial criminal law.",
